"n. 卫生学；卫生 【英】 n. 卫生学(the science of health and its maintenance) 【记】 来自希腊神话健康女 神 Hygeia; 【同】 参考：hygeian(健康 的，卫生的) n. 卫生学(提高健康、保持健康的科学); 保健法 【记】源于希腊神话中的健康女神Hygeia黑吉尼亚读: high gene－具有很high的gene基因, 因为很注意个人卫生. 【记】high + 音:洁,高度清洁→卫生；音：很洁，很清洁 hygiene (n.)  1670s, from French hygiène, ultimately from Greek hygieine techne ""the healthful art,"" from hygies ""healthy,"" literally ""living well"" (personified as the goddess Hygieia), from PIE *eyu-gwie-es- ""having a vigorous life."" The Greek adjective was used by Aristotle as a noun meaning ""health."""
